{RefSect1}
  {Title}Description{/Title}
{para}
This function reads a line of text from the given port.
The returned string is the contents of that line, not including
the terminating newline character.{/para}
{para}
If no characters can be read because the input port is at EOF,
then the EOF object is returned.  On the other hand, if EOF is
encountered after reading some characters but before reading
a newline character, then the EOF terminates the line and the
returned string will consist of the characters up to the EOF.{/para}
{/RefSect1}
